The claim by Kaduna State governor, Nasir el-Rufai, that the state was using N400,000 to treat a COVID-19 patient has been met with criticism by Nigerians. SaharaReporters had reported that el-Rufai during an executive committee meeting with traditional rulers on Tuesday said the amount was as a result of the increasing cost of drugs, feeding and personal protective equipment for doctors. Kaduna State Governor Nasir el-Rufai Following the revelation by the governor, Nigerians took to social media to condemn him for making such “outrageous claims”. See Also






